cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

This paper proposes a new attack against computer vision systems, specifically those used in autonomous vehicles. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The attack also involves modifying innocuous signs and advertisements, which could fall under the category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also mentions the use of optimization techniques, which could fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper includes experiments with physical and virtual settings, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia).
